<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gynasis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is is true that you can increase your defence (and thus you AC)skill if you get a mage or enchanter friend to dual you with their pet.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Benezetta PiaAdiuvo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes, it's quite true... any hit that you take that increases your Defense skill will cause a concurrent increase in your AC.<P>It's well worth the effort to max it out at 200.<P>Benezetta Pia`Adiuvo<BR>Tunarian Priestess of 53 Prayers<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Grumbles</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would also add that the safest pet to use in my experience is a necro pet, they respond well to commands where a enchanter pet wont be commanded at all.  And absolutely safest would be a necro + pet and necro has a pre-nerf insta cast circlet.  Then you can get the most out of your CH, and even work your weapons skills a bit, but if things get close, the necro casts shadows and poof- pet is dead<P><BR>Grumbles<BR>47 Cleric of Brell</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Adon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wow great tip!<P>Thanks guys<P>My defense is now at 185 (at level 48 so I need to work that thing!)<P>Will be dueling wife enchanter pet tonight!<P>Er wait...does the pet have to be blue for this to work????<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gynasis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I had heard that it does have to be blue.<P>Thanks for the info everyone. my defense so so low I am too ashamed to even say what it is. HeHe.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bristol_Torvo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I went through this at level 40 or 41.  My defense was LOW.  I think it was around 60ish.  So I took my enchanter and my cleric (2 computers) to the Neriak arena and spent about 8 or 9 hours getting defense all the way to 200.  Pet was dual wielding and hasted.  I always used a blue pet.  I liked using the arena because if I ever needed to stop and heal myself or the pet I could just step a little outside the arena and the pet stopped attacking.  <P>  I'm glad I did it because I got my AC from something like 500 up to 800 but I don't ever want to do it again.  What a pain.<P>The funny thing was that when I started the pet could beat me down pretty good.  As my defense and offense went up the tables turned and I was able to easily put the smack down on the pet.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Benezetta PiaAdiuvo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I wouldn't waste time dueling a green pet.  But I HAVE gotten defense, offense, and 1hb skill increases from green mobs. <BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xodd</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">OMG my skills are so low and I am already 54. They wont go up! Grrr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Viscera</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You get skill ups from a mob if you can get exp from it solo. So, for first or second level greenies, you will get skill ups.<P>Vis</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Selinar Crystalwind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Here's a hint I used when I realized I was level 53 and still missing 45 points of defense.  :/<P>Up until Level 53, there's a gnome merchant out in the West Freeport newbie area - I totally forget the name now, either Happ or Fizz?  Anyway, he's blue until 53, and while I don't suggest killing him, he hits pretty weak.  What I did was load myself up with full buffs, full AC gear, and full mana, then found a spot on the far southern side of the newbie area, right next to the EC zoneline, and cast a nuke at him.  He ran over, I moved around to get me against the wall and him directly in front of me, and just let him go to town.  Since you're against the wall, you can usually channel any heals you want, and I was able to stand there for up to 5 minutes at a time with well-timed Complete Heals.  I ended up getting a point every 15 minutes or so, but I think having a chanter friend cast Boon on you would help, as the 100 point bonus to Dex should increase the chance of a defense raise.<P>After 53?  Heh, well, remember that you can still get defense raises while DA'ed/DB'ed.  I've made a habit of being the 'last one out' on a train, and using DA/DB right at the zoneline, and having the whole train beat on me.  Since you can't be stunned under DA anymore, the odds of getting an increase are pretty good if you have 15 mobs beating you senseless.  Obviously, don't do this if you're evaccing, as DA will block ports.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tarf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My experience was that AGI gave faster defense rise.<P>Mith tunic, ranger or shammy buffs.<P>Fight low blue mobs, that way you get some exp, some loot and you do it with a friend with the same goal in mind, you have a safety net.  Druids make great companions for this sort of activity.  Shammys also, but slow is not desirable for this sort of thing, less hits = less chance of defense rise, but shammys can cast agi buff.  With a druid friend, you get damage shields, heals, roots, snares, but no agi buff   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
